# Constraints

<!--
This document captures non-negotiable conditions the system must satisfy.
Group constraints by type. Every constraint must have a rationale and an
impact statement — a constraint without a rationale will come back to bite
the architecture later when someone forgets *why* it is there.

Flexibility values:
  - hard       : must not be violated under any circumstance (legal, contract)
  - soft       : should not be violated without a recorded decision
  - negotiable : can be revisited if trade-offs change
-->

